`E.chain` / `E.chainW` is bind for `Either`: on `Right(a)` it runs your function `a -> Either<E', B>` and returns its result; on `Left(e)` it short-circuits. `E.chainW` is the widening form that lets each step have its own error type and unions them in the result.

